				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I helped a friend port a 6502 emulator to an atmega (AVR) back in 2006(?) and connected that to a SID chip (apperently just like kevtris), so yes it is possible.
<br />
<br />I remember though, that we had some problem with the memory. The emu tried to allocate a static 64KB array, which ofcause didn't fit in the MCu RAM. We found that we could substitute it to a linked list instead with linear access time. Sure a hashmap would have been better but it turned out that only &lt;20 bytes was used by most of the songs anyway so it didn't really matter.
<br />
<br />What i'm trying to say is that it works but you might want to add external memory if you want to run programs that use more memory than ~512Bytes. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /></div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

